This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it discusses the vulnerability of object detectors to adversarial examples. It may also belong to the sub-category of cybersecurity and privacy (cs.CR) as it discusses the potential security risks associated with the vulnerability of object detectors. Additionally, it may fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it discusses the limitations of deep learning algorithms and the need for improved defenses against adversarial attacks. Finally, it may also belong to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY) as it discusses the potential impact of adversarial attacks on safety-critical decisions.
